        - <span>BUSINESS</span>
        - <span role="byline">AGENCE FRANCE-PRESSE</span>
    </section>

    <p>En­crypted mes­sag­ing app Tele­gram will launch pay-for ser­vices next year, its Rus­sian-born founder Pavel Durov said Wed­nes­day, as the grow­ing com­pany needed “at least a few hun­dred mil­lion dol­lars per year”.</p>
    <p>“Tele­gram will be­gin to gen­er­ate rev­enue, start­ing next year,” Mr Durov said in a state­ment. “We will be able to launch count­less new fea­tures and wel­come bil­lions of new users.”</p>
    <p>Mr Durov, 36, said he did not plan to sell the com­pany and there­fore needed to look for other ways to come up with fund­ing.</p>


